\end_inset

, let's call it: r, is smaller or equal to the minimum weight of the fractional
 vertex cover 
\begin_inset Formula $m^{*}$
\end_inset

.
\begin_inset Newline newline
\end_inset


\begin_inset Formula $r=\begin{matrix}min\, & \sum f(v_{i})\\
s.t.\\
 & \text{for each \ensuremath{v_{i}v_{j}\in E,\,f(v_{i})+f(v_{j})\geq1}}
\end{matrix}$
\end_inset

 
\begin_inset Newline newline
\end_inset

If we denote the vector x to be f over all all vertices of G : 
\begin_inset Formula $x=f(V)$
\end_inset

 then : 
\begin_inset Formula $\begin{matrix}min\, & \sum f(v_{i})\\
s.t.\\
 & \text{for each \ensuremath{v_{i}v_{j}\in E,\,f(v_{i})+f(v_{j})\geq1}}
\end{matrix}=\begin{matrix}min\, & \boldsymbol{\vec{1}}\cdot x\\
s.t. & x_{i}\in\left\{ 0,1\right\} \\
 & \text{for each \ensuremath{v_{i}v_{j}\in E,\,x_{i}+x_{j}\geq1}}
\end{matrix}=m$
\end_inset


\begin_inset Newline newline
\end_inset

and so we get that 
\begin_inset Formula $m^{*}\leq m$
\end_inset

.
