\begin_inset Formula $x_{j}^{*}$
\end_inset

 are at least 0.5 and so at least one of 
\begin_inset Formula $x_{i}$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $x_{j}$
\end_inset

 are 1.
\begin_inset Newline newline
\end_inset


\begin_inset Formula $m\geq m^{*}=\sum_{i=1}^{\left|V\right|}x_{i}^{*}$
\end_inset

.
 
\begin_inset Newline newline
\end_inset

Since for each coordinate of 
\begin_inset Formula $x^{*}$
\end_inset

 at the very most we have multiplied it by 2 then the size of the provided
 vertex cover by the algorithm is : 
\begin_inset Formula $\sum_{i=1}^{\left|V\right|}x_{i}\leq\sum_{i=1}^{\left|V\right|}2x_{i}^{*}=2m^{*}\leq2m.$
\end_inset


